BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by YONHAP from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] NHK of Japan has reported that Japan notified the 
participants of the ROK, U.S., and Japan joint meeting held in 
Washington to discuss the North's nuclear issue that it is 
possible to discontinue Chongnyon [General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan]-affiliated Korean-Japanese residents' 
remittance of money to North Korea. 
  The broadcast noted that it was the first time the Japanese 
Government expressed an opinion about restricting the remittance 
of money to North Korea. It also added that the Japanese 
Government put forth its own proposal for imposing sanctions on 
North Korea, including restricting imports and exports and 
banning personal exchanges. 

